\title{Jon Sterling}
\author{jonmsterling}
\meta{author}{false}

\p{I am an \em{Associate Professor in Logical Foundations and Formal Methods} at [University of Cambridge](https://www.cst.cam.ac.uk/). I study programming languages and semantics using type theory, category theory, domain theory, and topos theory as a guide. My other interests include Near Eastern, Classical, and Germanic philology.}

\p{From 2021, I was a [Marie Sk≈Çodowska-Curie Postdoctoral Fellow](jms-0061) working with [Lars Birkedal](larsbirkedal); from 2016, I was a PhD student of [Robert Harper](robertharper) at Carnegie Mellon University. Previously, I received a B.A. in Linguistics from U.C. Berkeley.}

